          "name": "What is a VPN kill switch?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "A kill switch is a crucial security feature that instantly disconnects your device from the internet if the VPN connection drops unexpectedly, preventing your real IP address and unencrypted data from leaking."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Are free VPNs safe?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "While there are a few safe free tiers from reputable providers (like ProtonVPN), many free VPNs have been caught logging user data, injecting ads, or even selling bandwidth. Always use trusted free services and avoid completely unknown providers."
          }
        },
